<section class="sf card-section">

    <div class="card-container">
        <!-- Drip Irrigation -->
        <div class="card" id="dripIrrigationCard">
            <h5>Drip Irrigation</h5>
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1557129603-ff35a0c70e5e?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1974&q=80" />
            <p>
                Drip irrigation is a method of  delivering water directly to the roots of plants through a network of tubes, pipes and emitters. It involves the controlled release of small, consisteent amounts of water, minimising wastage and maximising water efficiency.<br /><br />
                <b>Benefit</b>: It enhances water efficiency, plant health, weed control, nutrient management, and conserves water resources.
            </p>
            <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="DripIrrigation">Learn More</a>
        </div>

        <!-- Organic Farming -->
        <div class="card" id="organicFarmingCard">
            <h5>Organic Farming</h5>
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1557129603-ff35a0c70e5e?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1974&q=80" />
            <p>
                Organic farming avoids synthetic chemicals and genetically modified organisms, relying on natural methods for pest control and soil health.<br /><br />
                <b>Benefit</b>: It is environmentally friendly, promotes healthier food, enhances biodiversity, supports sustainability, and offers resilience to environmental changes.
            </p>
            <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="OrganicFarming">Learn More</a>
        </div>

        <!-- Crop Rotation -->
        <div class="card" id="cropRotationCard">
            <h5>Crop Rotation</h5>
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1557129603-ff35a0c70e5e?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1974&q=80" />
            <p>
                Crop rotation is the practice of changing the type of crops grown in a specific field in a planned sequence.<br /><br />
                <b>Benefit</b>: Maintains soil fertility, minimises pest pressure, prevents soil depletion, enhances crop diversity and improves nutrient cycling.
            </p>
            <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="CropRotation">Learn More</a>
        </div>

        <!-- Rainwater Harvesting -->
        <div class="card" id="harvestingCard">
            <h5>Rainwater Harvesting</h5>
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1557129603-ff35a0c70e5e?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1974&q=80" />
            <p>
                Rainwater harvesting is the collection and storage of rainwater for various agricultural and non-agricultural purposes. It involves the use of tanks, reservoirs, and other systems to capture rainwater. <br /><br />
                <b>Benefit</b>: Reduces reliance on conventional water sources, conserves water, and provides a sustainable water supply for irrigation and livestock.
            </p>
            <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="RainwaterHarvesting">Learn More</a>
        </div>

        <!-- Mulching -->
        <div class="card" id="mulchingCard">
            <h5>Mulching</h5>
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1557129603-ff35a0c70e5e?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1974&q=80" />
            <p>
                Mulching is the practice of covering the soil with organic and synthetic material (mulch) to conserve moisture, suppress weed growth, and regulate soil temperature.<br /><br />
                <b>Benefit</b>: Protects water quality, prevents soil erosion, and reduces the movement of pollutants into water bodies.
            </p>
            <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Mulching">Learn More</a>
        </div>

        <!-- Contour Farming -->
        <div class="card" id="reducingFoodWasteCard">
            <h5>Reducing Food Waste</h5>
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1557129603-ff35a0c70e5e?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1974&q=80" />
            <p>
                Contour farming is a technique where crops are planted and tilled parallel to contour lines of a slope. It helps prevent soil erosion by slowing down the flow of water.<br /><br />
                <b>Benefit</b>: Minimises soil erosion, improves water retention, and maintains soil fertility on sloping terrain.
            </p>
            <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="ReducingFoodWaste">Learn More</a>
        </div>

        <!-- Hydroponics and Aquaponics -->
        <div class="card" id="hydroponicsAquaponicsCard">
            <h5>Hydroponics and Aquaponics</h5>
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1557129603-ff35a0c70e5e?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1974&q=80" />
            <p>
                Hydroponics is a soilless farming method that grows plants in nutrient-rich water.
                Aquaponics combines hydroponics with fish farming, utilising fish waste to fertilise the plants.<br /><br />
                <b>Benefit</b>: Efficient water and resource use, reduced pesticide use, and year-round production in controlled environments.
            </p>
            <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="HydroponicsAquaponics">Learn More</a>
        </div>

        <!-- Natural Pest Management -->
        <div class="card" id="pestManagementCard">
            <h5>Natural Pest Management</h5>
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1557129603-ff35a0c70e5e?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1974&q=80" />
            <p>
                Natural pest management involves the use of natural predators, parasites and beneficial insects to control pests without the use of synthetic pesticides<br /><br />
                <b>Benefit</b>: Reduces chemical pesticide use, maintains ecological balance, and prevents pest outbreaks.
            </p>
            <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="NaturalPestManagement">Learn More</a>
        </div>

        <!-- Composting -->
        <div class="card" id="compostingCard">
            <h5>Composting</h5>
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1557129603-ff35a0c70e5e?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1974&q=80" />
            <p>
                Composting is the natural breakdown of organic materials into nutrient rich product that can be used to enrich soil. <br /><br />
                <b>Benefit</b>: Improves soil health, reduces waste, lessens chemical dependency, enhances water retention and controls erosion.
            </p>
            <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Composting">Learn More</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>